node.title: NT records no new cases of COVID-19 overnight following nine Binjari cases
node.alt: Michael Gunner at a COVID press conference on November 18, 2021.
node.description: The Chief Minister says the Northern Territory has recorded no new cases of coronavirus overnight after nine new cases were detected in the remote community of Binjari on Saturday evening.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded no new case of COVID-19 overnight,\u00a0Chief Minister Michael Gunner says.", "On Saturday night the NT government announced\u00a0nine new cases of COVID-19 have\u00a0been detected in\u00a0the Binjari community\u00a0on the outskirts of Katherine.", "Binjari and the nearby Rockhole community were immediately sent into a\u00a0\"hard\" lockdown following the announcement of the cases, the NT government yesterday announced.", "Under a hard lockdown\u00a0residents are only able to leave their homes and yards for medical treatment or in an emergency.", "At a press conference today Mr Gunner said the nine Binjari cases come from six different households.", "The vaccination status of those infected is not known, he said.\u00a0", "One case, a 78-year-old woman,\u00a0was taken to Royal Darwin Hospital on Saturday night.", "Mr Gunner said the other eight cases had all been transported to Howard Springs overnight for monitoring and care.", "Some of those, he said,\u00a0had existing health conditions.", "Mr Gunner said the cases in Binjari were \"very concerning but not surprising\"\u00a0after\u00a0COVID-19 fragments were detected in the community\u00a0on Friday.", "Cases in the community, and possibly in Rockhole, could increase by \"a lot\" in coming days, Mr Gunner said.", "There were 3,005 tests processed in the Northern Territory in 24 hours, Mr Gunner said.", "More to come."]
